climatePledgeFriendly.details: OEKO-TEX STANDARD 100 requires textiles-based products to be tested against a list of 1,000+ chemicals, to limit those which may be harmful to human health. Certification focus: #ProductSafety and #ChemicalsUsed. The Forest Stewardship Council certified products support responsible forestry, helping keep forests healthy for future generations.

features: SUSTAINABLE PLANT BASED DIAPERS: Naty Diapers are the only diapers that prevents your baby’s skin to get in contact with plastic materials. They are free of toxins and chemicals, and are only made from plant based materials.

COMFORTABLE AND ABSORBENT: Our Eco Diapers are created with your baby in mind, as well as the planet. These natural diapers are breathable on the skin with a comfortable flex-fit while also providing premium protection with absorbent fibers.

HYPOALLERGENIC DIAPERS FOR SENSITIVE SKIN: When it comes to your baby, especially if they’re a newborn, hypoallergenic products can make all the difference. Plant-based means fewer allergens and irritants, helping eliminate diaper rash.

ECO-FRIENDLY AND COMPOSTABLE: Traditional disposable diapers are often made with toxic plastics. Naty Eco Diapers are mostly made from certified plant based materials like sugar cane, corn, woodpulp and cotton which makes them natural, absorbent, and remarkably soft. Sizes available include newborn diapers up to size 6 diapers.

GOOD FOR BABY, GOOD FOR NATURE: Eco by Naty was first started in Sweden nearly 27 years ago. Today, we continue with our goal to create products that are not only safe for our bodies, but that are also good for the environment. Our High-Tech Eco Products are backed by independent sustainability certifications, we offer the greenest products, all made from nature!
body.description: With 0 percent oil-based plastic on skin, Eco by Naty diapers have the softest touch on your baby's skin. Plant-based fibers ensure that the diaper breathes and provides a comfortable fit so that even the most delicate skin does not get any diaper rash. The high plant-based content is unique as it is the only diaper in the market to receive 'OK biobased' certification from TUV Austria. The diapers core consist primarily of premium wood pulp that is highly absorbent keeping your baby's skin dry and protected against leakages and blowouts. This makes our diapers ideal to be used both daytime and nighttime. As a parent, you do not want your baby to be in contact with any chemicals or irritant materials that are harmful to your baby's skin, which is why Eco by Naty's diapers are Hypoallergenic and Dermatologically tested. Our diapers are free from fragrances/perfumes, chlorine, bleaching, latex, lotions and are certified by OEKO-TEX Standard 100 to be free from over 100 harmful substances, ensuring our diapers are also suitable for babies with the most sensitive skin. At Eco by Naty we believe how we produce our diapers is just as important as the materials we use. This is why we source our wood pulp from FSC certified forests. The FSC certification ensures that the forest is managed in a sustainable eco-friendly manner and at the same time taking into account local, societal, indigenous and workers interests. We have been awarded the Vegan label as our diapers are free from animal testing nor contain any animal derived ingredients. The packaging is certified 3 stars (of 4) for its renewability by TUV Austria. The Eco by Naty diaper range is available from Newborn / Preemie to size 1,2,3,4,5 and 6. Each diaper size has adorable Scandinavian inspired design prints, and of course are free from heavy metals.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Did not work for us BUT great product/amazing customer service
reviews.reviewText: I loved these diapers and I had such high hopes that they would work for us. We gave them an honest try. They are well made and I love that they are eco and skin friendly. My son (now 3 months) has very sensitive skin. These did not irritate him at all. Unfortunately, these leaked with every single use, within 2 pees our son was soaked. We think these just did not fit our son well, he is short and chunky. I really think if they had fit our son better we would have stuck with them. I gave the ones we were not going to use to a friend and they have loved them and had no issues with leaks, their baby is more long and thin than ours. Great product, and I cannot say enough good things about their customer service. I reached out to them to ask for a refund since the diapers had not worked, they sent me a new package of a new size to try, which unfortunately still did not work for us. But, It was less than a week between my first email to customer service and receiving the new package of diapers. That goes a long way. I would recommend trying these diapers, just know the fit may not work depending on your baby's size! :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not what they used to be
reviews.reviewText: This was my favorite brand when my son was born in 2018. I used Eco by Naty exclusively up until he turned 4. Then I got what seemed to be a new version of their pull-ups and got disappointed by the fit (too much material between the legs). When my daughter was born in January I got her Naty newborn diapers and the fit was way off, super wide and also loose in the back. I decided to give it another try 6 months later and got Naty diapers in size 3 (after trying and not liking Coterie) but the fit of size 3 was still disappointing. I do want to give them credit for their absorbancy, even though they are on the thinner side now; and I like that the surface stays relatively dry.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought these diapers because they were voted one of the top “eco friendly” options. Firstly I want to note that if making earth friendly decisions is important to you, there are MUCH better options than this brand. They are made with better plastics maybe than normal plastic diapers but there is no recycling, no composting, and no biodegrading planned with these. They are hardly a step up from the regular disposable plastic diapers. To top this off, I purchased these diapers additionally because out of the “green” options, these ones listed the smallest size as fitting 4-11lb babies. These diapers BEGAN fitting at 11lbs, and are strangely shaped so have never fit perfectly. So now that the baby is big enough to fit the diapers, she is big enough that the absorbency is inadequate for her. She is leaking through EVERY. SINGLE. TIME. These diapers have failed on every level. Eco friendly? Not really. Fit? Absolutely not. Absorbs? Nope.Please save yourself the time and frustration and buy a different brand.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Love them but…..
reviews.reviewText: These are super soft and don’t have that plastic feel to them. I love that they don’t have a “scent” to them. Only downfall is they run super small. My little one is 8lbs and 4ozs and I got him a size one that’s from 4-11lbs and they are small. They are short on the back of him and the sides of the thigh poo will get through. I would recommend to size up as they seem to run small!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Loved these diapers for my older babies, HATE the infant sizes
reviews.reviewText: Don't bother using these until your baby is in at least a size 3. The newborn / very young infant sizes are trash. They are oddly shaped and don't contour to baby's body well at all, causing leaks and blowouts every. single. time.I didn't start using them right after birth with my twins ten years ago so I only had experience with the bigger sizes until my newest baby came. I was gifted a couple of packs of sizes one and two and size one was pure trash. Dumbest diaper ever. So poorly designed that it's actually unbelievable that they sell them. Size two was a slightly better fit, but still leaked and caused blowouts. And yes, my baby was well within the reccomended weight for the sizes. I accidentally ordered an entire box of size ones, but thankfully Amazon refunded me. Now I'm stuck with the worst diapers on the planet (that belong in the trash) because there is no way I would do that to a new mom so I can't in good conscience even give them to anyone.I grew frustrated with them, especially considering the price, and switched to cloth diapers. I am enjoying cloth diapering so much and as much as I loved Naty ten years ago, there is no going back from cloth.For those of you considering cloth diapers, KaWaii Baby pocket diapers are the best. Hands-down. Their great prices can't be beat and I find them to be even better quality than my more expensive ($20+ a piece) diapers. Nora's Nursery has beautiful colors and prints, but the quality is not nearly as good as KaWaii Baby and the elastic is way too tight. I have four of them and I hate them. I say that because Nora's is one of the best-selling cloth diaper brands on Amazon. Save yourself lots of time (and some money) and go directly to the KaWaii Baby Diaper site because they offer free shipping, but not on Amazon for some reason.Happy diapering!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best diaper for sensitive premie baby
reviews.reviewText: My son was born premie and has skin irritation to so many diapers. I’ve tried pampers, honest, seventh generation, dypers, momcozy, babycozy. I can say Eco by Naty is the best one. So soft and thin (aeration) plus no leaks! Cute and clean design. No rash at low back from those stretch pleats. No rash from the adhesive strips cutting into groin area. HelloBello is another good premie diaper, but the material is not as soft as Eco. Love love this diaper!!
This is no for me it’s not that good my son feel itchy and it’s not that soft

Uso questi pannolini sin dalla nascita della mia seconda figlia che adesso ha 8 mesi e devo dire di esserci trovati molto bene, nessuna irritazione e molto assorbenti anche per tutta la notte. Non da meno il minore impatto ambientale rispetto ai classici pannolini… uno dei tanti modi che ognuno può attuare per fare la propria parte nel rispetto dell’ambiente!L’unico piccolo “neo” a mio avviso è la vestibilità ridotta. Nel complesso comunque CONSIGLIATI!

Aunque parezca que salen caros, luego absorben más que los de marca blanca y, por lo tanto duran más en la absorción de pipis. Personalmente estoy contenta con el resultado. Aun así sale a cuenta comprarlos por Amazon (por la web salen más caros).
Très bon produit, attache solide et le découpage de la couche partie avant permet de ne pas accrocher le reste du cordon de bébé.
